				<div class="postbody">
				Social Security Simplified
<br />

<br />
1.  Take from the young and poor and give to the old and rich.  Old people vote, and young people don't, so this works out great.  Being old, I expect to be rich soon as the government gives me your money.
<br />

<br />
2.  Let everyone know they can spend like drunken sailors because Uncle Sam will protect you in your old age.  Encourage irresponsibility.  Why save?
<br />

<br />
3.  It's a pay-as-you-go plan, aka Ponzi scam.  Instead of a conventional retirement account, with real assets accumulated over time, current workers pay the bills of current retirees.
<br />

<br />
There, that's not so hard to understand, is it?
<br />

<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /><br />
