			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Kill it. Replace it with...
<br />

<br />
1) Government REQUIRES you to set aside a portion of your pay for retirement in some kind of investment or retirement account. You do not have the option to opt-out of this. If necessary, the government will have it taken out of your paycheck directly.
<br />

<br />
2) There is a MINIMUM you can contribute, but no maximum. The actual total will be up to you.
<br />

<br />
3) Any money going into this retirement investment goes in pre-tax. As long as it is withdrawn after retirement age (or under whatever guidelines an economist smarter than I am can come up with), you get it tax free.
<br />

<br />
4) YOU choose the retirement investment. The government can help you by providing you a list and education on what the various kinds of retirement investments are and how they work, but in the end you are the one who has to choose where and how to invest for your retirement.
<br />

<br />
